-1 RULES~
The rules (brief):
Ignorance is NOT an excuse! THIS IS YOUR WARNING TO ADHERE TO THE RULES.


There are no second chances.

1) This is a Player Kill mud.
2) Respect the Immortal Staff. 
3) No Multiplaying.
4) No EXP or Quest Botting.
5) No Whining.
6) No going link dead.
7) No killing mortal avatars. Wait until they are classed.
8) You have 5 IRL minutes to decapitate someone after you mort them.
9) No Advertisement for other muds.
10) No Pbashing

For a detailed explanation, see 'help rules2'
Also see 'help policy1' and 'help policy2' and 'help disclaimer'

~

-1 RULES2~
The Commandments:
1)  #RThis is a Player Kill mud#n. So kill.  Don't whine to an imm about
    getting killed unless it was because of cheating.  And make sure you 
    know what we mean by cheating because we will deal harshly with those 
    that slander.
2)  #RRESPECT#n 
    The Immortal staff on this mud, as on any mud is to be respected.
    Failure to do so can get you banned.  The staff chosen to administer    
    this mud have been chosen for a reason. Slander of an immortal is a 
    lack of respect.  Those found to engage in such activity need not mud
    here. This is a no-tolerance issue., and also includes bugging for an imm
    position.
 3) #RNo MULTIPLAYING.#n 
    If you have two characters logged in at one time, action will be
    taken. You may find yourself with one less character.  Also included
    in Multiplay is the sharing of gear or knowledge between 2 characters
    of the same player.
4)  #RBOTTING.#n  
    Botting is allowed as long as you are an avatar, and in a place where
    anyone can kill you.  You can Stance bot.  You can spell bot.  You can
    NOT experience or quest bot.  If we catch you exp or quest botting, you 
    will be dealt with appropriately.
5)  #RNO WHINING.#n
    Bringing up suggestions or pointing out a flaw in the system is okay.
    If you see an injustice, or a problem post a RESPECTFUL note.
    We WILL try to take care of it.
6)  #RNO DROPPING CARRIER#n
    (Going Link dead in combat) In the middle of a fight, we know it may 
    occur at times, however if the only time you go link dead is when you
    are about to die, that is considered cheating... Also included in this
    is quitting to avoid paradox.
7)  #RNO KILLING MORTAL AVATARS.#n
    In any way.
8)  This is a PK mud, PK is a good thing.  PKing and keeping someone
    morted is not.  If you KILL someone, tie and
    DECAPITATE them.  Don't keep them morted or tied.  We are all here to
    have fun, not be tortured.  You get 5 IRL minutes.
    After 5 minutes of being morted, the player had either be cap'd or let go.
9)  #RNO Advertisment of other muds.#n  This needs to be done in private --
    not in channels, titles, descriptions, bios, or note boards. 
10) #RNo Player bashing#n
    In Character comments are acceptable.  However, this is up to the 
    discression of the immortals. If there is ANY doubt if the comment
    was In Character, or Out Of Character,  We will always side on
    "Out Of Character". This DOES include "your mom, dad, sister, uncle"
    type nonsense.

ALSO READ "help Policy1" and "help Policy2"!!
~

-1 POLICY1~
* #RCloning of Anything is Banned.#n

  Cloning of ANY artifact or any gear, or questpoints will result in 
  deletion of your character and possiable banning of your site.
  Only exceptions are when using the vamp power 'clone' to clone MUD items, (meaning items 
  naturally found in the mud, NOT created by any means) and mages using the 'create' written
  spell.

  
* #RNo spamming ANY channels, including private ones.#n

  This is unfriendly and upsets people. The penalty for this is that the 
  offending player will be silenced for a period determined by the immortal.

* #RNo swearing.#n

  We will not tolerate the use of foul language on public channels. If you
  feel the need to swear, do it in tells or whispers, and don't spam it!
  We try not to be TOO strict about this, but don't push it.  It would 
  also be wise to NEVER swear at or to an imm, personal or otherwise.   

* No transferring of any class relics to different classes. (ex. Demon
  longswords to mages. Etc etc.)

* No Harassment of imms off or on the mud. If you have a problem with an 
  imm, please speak to a higher imm in a calm tone. Or you will not be
  heard. 

* Playing this mud requirements common sense, do not abuse bugs, do not
  try to dodge punishments by technicalities. That only gets you less
  respected by the imms, and players. 

** READ HELP POLICY2 ~

-1 POLICY2~
* #RPurposely CRASHING the mud and hacking passwords.#n

  Deliberate crashing of the mud will cause you to be denied or possibly
  deleted and may even end up in your site being prevented from connecting
  to the mud (banned).  Your ISP admin might also be informed of your action.
  The ISP that runs this site will definitely be informed. 
  Also keep in mind that THREATENING to crash or hack the mud will be treated
  the same as if you actually did so.
 
* #RSharing characters.#n

  Is not allowed. Meaning don't give your character to someone else.
  Meaning two different ppl may not have access to the same character.

* #RStorage of Artifacts#n 

  This is considered MultiPlaying.
  You are not allowed to place your artifact(s) on a "storage character"
  Any storage characters found will be deleted and the artifact(s) they
  were storing will be placed back in the game at the immortals discression.

** #RIf you don't like any or all of these rules or policies leave this site now.#n

~

