-1 DAMAGE~
When someone attacks someone else, a damage message is displayed to give 
you an idea of how much damage you have caused.  The following messages 
represent the following amounts of damage.

If you missed, then you did 0 points of damage.
If you lightly hit, then you did 1 to 25 points of damage.   
If you hit, then you did 26 to 50 points of damage.
If you hit hard, then you did 51 to 100 points of damage.
If you hit very hard, then you did 101 to 250 points of damage.
If you hit extremely hard, then you did 251 to 500 points of damage.
If you hit incredibly hard, then you did 500 or more points of damage.

You final blow will be a death move, depending on your weapon type.
~

-1 CLAIM CALL GIFT LOCATE~
Syntax: claim <object>
Syntax: call <object>
Syntax: call all
Syntax: gift <object> <player>
Syntax: locate

By claiming an object (which costs 500 exp), that object becomes your 
personal property.  Using the 'locate' command you can find what items 
currently belong to you and where they are in the mud.  If you are not 
carrying the item, you can get it back by calling it with the 'call' 
command.  You can change the ownership of your own items by use of the 
'gift' command.
~

0 WEAPON WEAPONS~
These are some weapons you can use to train the weapons skill listed.
They are not the best weapon of any one skill,  but they will train
the skill listed.

Unarmed - remove weapons, or British's sceptre.
Slash   - a black shimmering longsword.
Slice   - a holy Avenger.
Stab    - poseidon's Trident.
Whip    - a dragon tailed whip.
Claw    - a red dragon claw.
Blast   - an assault shotgun.
Pound   - a small club.
Crush   - a hammer.
Grep    - A Salvnos forged grepper.
Bite    - tusks, or fangs.
Pierce  - a long slim dagger.
Suck    - a Hoover vacuum cleaner.
~

0 NINJA NINJAS~
Ninjas are masters of the night and darkness. Though mortal, they have their own 
unique ways of surviving in the world of vampires and demons. Each ninja studies 
under three principles of life, Sora - *Heaven*, Chikyu - *Earth*, and 
Ningenno - *Humanity*. Mastery of these principles account for the stealth
and strength of the ninjae.

Sora - *Heaven* This is the finding, observing, and learning about one's target.

1: Mitsukeru -Locate- The scrying power to find enemies
2: Koryou -Consider- The read aura power, learn of your enemies
3: Kakusu -Hidden- Enhanced hide. Only other ninjas can see you
4: Uro-Uro -Silent Walk- You leave no footprints behind
5: Kanzuite -Aware- The truesight power (unable to go through some vamp/wolf powers)
6: Bomuzite -Sleep Gas- By mixing a potion, you may put a person to sleep
7: Mizotamouyo -Shadowwalk- You are able to walk the paths of shadows to reach your target
8: Kakusite -Mask- Able to disguise yourself as other players (mask target)

Chikyu - *Earth* The preparation for battle

1: Tsuyoku -Strength- Ninja toughness
2: Songai -Damage- Enchanced damage
3: Isogu -Haste- Adds two extra attacks
4: Tsuiseki -Hunt- Fast hunting
5: Sakeru -Sonic Speed- Dodge more efficiently
6: HaraKiri -Blood Power- Hurt yourself to gain power
7: Orimasu -Mending- Regenerate your being through willpower alone
8: Gunaya -Web- Entrap your foes with a spiritual net

Ningenno - *Humanity* This is the Battle, Attacking, and getting away

1: Tsume -Claw- IronClaw worn on wrist to aid in fighting
2: Hakunetsu -First Strike- You get super backstabs
3: Mienaku -Vanish- Never fail flee (blinds)
4: Shiroken -Throwing Star- Added attack per round
5: Dokuyaku -Poison- Adds poisons to the Shiroken
6: Circle -Circle- Move around your opponents to hit them from behind
7: Trip -Trip- Trip your opponent and send them to the ground

*Ninja Armor* type 'ninjaarmor' to buy.

Note: All these skills require the japanese name to be used, except for trip, 
circle, Gunaya, Kakusite. To use these, simply type the name that is in the 
brackets.
~

0 PROTEAN~

This Discipline allows a vampire to transform either their entire body or 
a part of their body into something inhuman.  The vampire can thus grow 
claws, turn into a bat, transform into a wolf or dissolve into a fine 
mist.  A vampire can use most other Disciplines while shapeshifted, but 
may not cast spells.  Full transformation is not possible during combat, 
although claws can be grown if you are fighting.  While shapeshifted the 
vampire cannot wear any equipment.

The powers available to this Discipline are as follows:
[*]	Nightsight - The vampire is able to see normally after dark, without 
	any light source. When this is activated the Beast makes itself evident 
	in the vampire's red glowing eyes. 

[**] 	Claws - This lets the vampire sprout long claws on each hand, like those 
	of a beast. They can rend flesh and armour alike and they inflict 
	aggravated wounds. 

[***] 	Earthmeld - When a vampire calls forth this power they can actually 
	meld with and become one with the earth. Onlookers see the vampire 
	actually sink into the bare ground.

[****] 	Change: Allow the vampire to transform into bat, wolf or mist.  Bat 
	form can fly and detect almost everything (invis, hidden, etc).  While in 
	wolf form, the vampire enjoys the benefit of an extra 500hp and greatly 
	enhanced combat abilities.  Mist form is impervious to attacks and can 
	pass through doors.  Beware though, for two vampires in mist form CAN 
	attack each other.

[*****] Spiritform - Turns the vampires body translucent and insubstancial.
~

0 CELERITY~

This Discipline explains the legendary superior quickness of vampires.  
They have the ability to move with amazing speed and become little more than a blur
to mortal eyes, obviously such an ability is extremely useful allowing the vampire to
hit and dodge faster than lesser opponents. Typing 'celerity renew' will renew your
celerity while you are still fighting.
~

0 FORTITUDE~

Fortitude describes a type of supernatural toughness and vigor which
allows Kindred to resist harm.  Many vampires are very tough and are able
to withstand a lot of injury inflicted by weapons and spells.  However 
with the Fortitude power, they resist damage even further by often keeping 
the weapons from harming them at all.
~

0 POTENCE~

This Discipline defines the superior strength that vampires often 
possess.  This physical might allows the user to inflict much larger 
amounts of damage in combat than normal.
~

0 OBFUSCATE~

Kindred with this Discipline excel at hiding among and away from crowds.  
When they do not wish to be seen, others rarely notice them even if they 
are standing in plain view.  Though this Discipline affects others minds 
and does not actually render the users invisible, the end result is much 
the same.  Obfuscate is the opposing Discipline to Auspex, and they 
cancel out many of each others powers.

Kindred with this power gain the following advantages:
[*]	Vanish - This allows a vampire to move around without being seen, 
	shadows seem to	cling to him and people avert their eyes as they pass, 
	not even remembering that something was there. As the discipline increases 
	so does its potency. 

[**] 	Mask 'Target' - A vampire using this power can alter somebody's perception so 
	entirely that they believe that they are actually seeing someone completely 
	different. 

[****] 	Shield - When a vampire activates this ability he effectively shields his 
	aura and his mind from prying perceptions making it impossible to locate them
	through supernatural means. 

[*****]	Soulmask - Not all disguises are skin deep. With this power the vampire can
	not only completely shield his aura but also give forth false information about
	himself making others believe that he is far more powerful, or weaker, than 
	in fact he actually is.
~

0 OBTENEBRATION~

Obtenebration allows the user to manipulate the powers of darkness.  By 
using their powers they are able to switch between the normal world and 
the plane of shadows at will.  They may also view things in both planes 
simultaneously if they so wish.

This Discipline allows the following powers:
[*]	Shroud - The vampire can blanket a whole area with an impenetrable inky 
	blackness, a darkness deeper than a moonlit night, anyone caught by 
	such a shroud will find it both disturbing and disorientating. 

[**]	Arms 'target' - This allows a vampire to call forth "tentacles" of solid 
	darkness from the shadows around him. These tentacles will then grasp 
	and restrain the vampires foes. 

[***] 	Shadowbody - This lets the vampire turn their body into a slithering, 
	undulating shadow, vampires that use this power are virtually invulnerable 
	while in this form. 

[****] 	Lamprey 'target' - This acutally calls forth the Darkness to strike the 
	vampires opponents, draining their blood from them as they stand and fight. 

[*****]	Shadowstep - The vampire may step into human-sized shadows and exit another
	of similar size in another locale with this power. However shadows 
	require darkness, which can only be found in darkened rooms.
~

0 SERPENTIS~

Serpentis is the art of temptation and corruption.  Vampires with this 
Discipline have the ability to tear out their own hearts, rendering 
themselves immune to being staked.  Serpentis users also gain the ability 
to transform themselves into a giant serpent and back at will. 

[*] 	Tongue 'target' - The vampire with this ability may lengthen their tongue
	at will, splitting it into a fork like that of a serpent. It can actually 
	reach out as far as 18 inches and makes a terrifying weapon in combat. 

[**] 	Mummify - This allows the user to actually mummify himself, shriveling 
	into an almost invulnerable form. This induces a stated similar to torpor, 
	rendering the user completely immobile. 

[***] 	Serpent - The vampire may change his form into that of a huge serpernt. 
	It weighs as much as the vampire's human form and streches over eight feet
	long. This grants the vampire considerable advantages. 

[****] 	Darkheart - With this ability the vampire may pull his heart from his body. 
	This means that they cannot then be staked. 

[*****]	Breath - This lets the vampire call forth on their inner corruption and to
	spew it forth in a poisonous cloud of taint. This airborne poison is 
	powerful enough to wither trees	and even corrode stone. It will stike everyone 
	in the room, dealing damage to all of them.
~

0 AUSPEX~

This Discipline is one of extrasensory awareness, empathy and 
perception.  Those using this Discipline tend to be strongly affected by 
environmental phenomena.  Vampires with Auspex are able to see and sense 
things most other people cannot.  Auspex is the opposing Discipline to 
Obfuscate, and they cancel out many of each others powers.

This Discipline allows the following powers:
[*] 	Heighten - By sharpening all of their five senses the vampire is able to 
	detect a wide variety of beings and objects that would usually lay
	hidden to mortals, this power is tightly interwoven with the discipline 
	and the range of things that can be detected increases as the discipline does. 

[**] 	Readaura 'target' - This enables the vampire to detect and read the mystical 
	halos that surround all beings, the colours that they see tell them much and 
	give them insight into how powerful their targets are. At higher levels 
	this power may be extended to discover detailed	information about objects 
	that the vampire possesses. 

[***] 	Unveil 'target' - By forming a bridge between their mind and another's, 
	the vampire may	actually read the thoughts of their target, "stolen" 
	thoughts are as audible to the vampire as normal speech. 

[****] 	Astral - At this level of mastery the vampire can expand their senses beyond 
	their physical body and travel quickly to any place or person that they can
	imagine. Use [<command> and [move <target>. 

[*****]	Scry and scry 'target' - By concentrating on a single person the vampire can
	actually see through their eyes and see exactly where they are, also the 
	vampire can spread their concentration across a large area and gain an insight 
	into the location of many different people, unless the intended target has
	supernatural protection of some kind.

[*****]	Mindblast - Alows the vampire to use the power of his mind to stun a victim.

[*****]	Omnipotence - Alows the vampire to create a spectral eye to follow a
	target.  Comman the eye by using [.
~

0 ANIMALISM~

[*] 	Pigeon 'target' - A vampire with this power may command a pigeon to carry 
	an object that he possesses and give it to another player or mob. 

[**] 	Beckon 'target' - This gives the ability to call out in the voice of a 
	specific type of animal and summon it to you, they may not offer immediate
	assistance to the vampire but they will be favorably disposed. Horses, frogs,
	ravens, cats, dogs and yaks may be called upon.

[***] 	Song 'target' - Vampires are the supreme predators of the natural world, most
	vampires believe that within each of them lies the spirit of a ravenous beast,
	similar to the beast that lies in mortal hearts. With this power the vampire 
	may reach out to a mortal and and briefly connect their bestial spirits, 
	that brief contact may be enough to supress the	targets beast and make them 
	less likely to attack. 

[****] 	Share 'target' - This allows the vampire to reach out with his mind and to
	move into the mind of a beckoned animal and to thus share it. The animal 
	can then be given controlled using [. 

[*****]	Beast 'target' - With this level of animalism, the vampire has a good
	understanding of the beast within, this allows them to fling the spirit of 
	the beast out of their body and	into that of another. This makes the recipient 
	immediately overcome by frenzy. This power can also be turned inward to 
	release the power of the vampire's beast in all of it's fury.

[*****]	Succulence - Increase the quailty of a targets blood.

[*****]	Frenzy - Puts the beast in control of your actions, increases your rage. 
 ~

0 THAUMATURGY~

[*] 	Taste 'target' - This was developed as a means for gauging the strengths
	of a vampire's opponents. By tasting their blood the vampire may glean
	infomation as to their blood pool and if the target is a vampire their
	generation and which disciplines they have. 

[**] 	Bloodrage 'target' - This allows the vamipre to cause another vamipre to
	use blood against their will, thus weakening them, the slightest touch is 
	all that is needed to use this power. But it also has the side effect
	that the target is likely to fly into an insane frenzy as a result. 

[***] 	Potency - The vampire may concentrate his own blood, causing it to become 
	more potent, effectively lowering his generation. 

[****] 	Theft 'target' - A vampire that possesses this power may siphon the very
	life essence from a target. They can mystically drain the blood from them 
	without ever actually touching them. The blood is transferred directly
	into the thaumaturgist as if they had drunk directly. 

[*****]	Cauldron 'target' - This devastating attack causes the blood of an
	intended victim to boil like water over a flame. The vampire touches his
	target causing the blood to simmer within their veins. Unless the target
	has some kind of mystical heat resisitance death is virtually assured. 
~

0 NECROMANCY~

[*] 	Thanatopsis 'target' - By examining corpses the vampire is able to learn 
	much about the final moments of their lives, they may glean valuable 
	information such as where they were killed and by who. 

[*] 	Spiriteyes - Alows the vampire to see into the umbra.

[**] 	Preserve 'target corpse' - This allows the vampire to slow the ravages 
	of time on a corpse or a limb so that it will never decay. 

[***] 	Spiritgate 'target' - The vampire with this power gains the ability to 
	form a portal through the spirit world to the location of the corpses death.  

[****] 	Spiritguardian - This summons a guardian spirit to you which has the power 
	to alert you to those who attempt to use supernatural powers on you. 

[*****]	Zombie 'target' - By feeding a corpse some of its blood, the vampire can
	bring it back to a state of unlife which is much as it was in life, but 
	due to the Blood Oath the zombie will be as a servant to its creator. 
~

0 PRESENCE~

[*] 	Awe - Awe is very simple, once it is activated people want to be close to 
	the vampire, and they find it harder to attack them. However it is not so 
	powerful that it overrides their sense of self-preservation. 

[**] 	Dreadgaze 'target' - This calls forth unbearable terror in its victims, 
	and it sends them into a reckless flight. 

[***] 	Entrance 'target' - By using this power the vampire can turn others into 
	his willing servants. Out of what seems to them true devotion they follow 
	and obey the vampires commands. 

[****] 	Summoning 'target' - With this power a vampire can call out to someone and 
	bring them forth from wherever they are, no matter how large the distance, 
	providing they have their summon on. 

[*****]	Majesty - This heightens the presence mystique a thousandfold. This inspires
	respect and devotion, or fear, in everyone that the vampire meets, rendering 
	them unable to harm the vampire in any way. 
~

0 VICISSITUDE~

[*] 	Changeling 'target' - A vampire with this power may alter their body 
	parameters, such things are cosmetic and minor in scope but may let them 
	actually resemble their target. 

[**] 	Fleshcraft mod 'target' 'modification' - This allows the vampire to perform 
	drastic, grotesque alterations. Only flesh (including fat, muscle and 
	cartilage) may be transformed but the change is permanent. Fins, wings 
	and tails can be formed. 

[***] 	Bonecraft mod 'target' 'modification' - This terrible power allows the 
	vampire to manipulate bone in the same manner that flesh is shaped. 
	Combined with fleshcraft this allows truely drastic alterations to me 
	made enabling the target to be made to look like virtually anything (bone
	<whateveryouwant>), also tusks, horns and exoskeletons can be pulled out 
	of the targets body. 

[****] 	Zuloform - The vampire who employs this power becomes the scariest monster, 
	the dread Zulo of Balkan peasants' terrified whispers. The vampire increased 
	to become eight feet tall; their skin changes to a grayish-black chitin; 
	the arms become apelike, tipped with ragged black nails; and the face warps 
	into something out of a nightmare. 

[*****]	Plasmaform - The blood is more than life to a vampire with this power, for
	they can physically transform themselves into sentient vitae. It is as 
	normal blood, but it contains the very essence of the vampire.   
~

0 OBEAH~

* 	Obeah: Open your third eye

[*]	Panacea 'target' - clots their wounds.

[**] 	Anesthetic 'target' - makes victim take no pain penalties until midnight. 

[***] 	Neutral - makes room a safe room, for a certain length of time :) 

[****] 	Unburden - lowers target beast, can't go below true beast, and will only 
	take you down to 1. 

[*****]	Renew 'target' - complete heal including growing bits back. 
~

0 QUIETUS~

[*] 	Silence - When invoked, this power surrounds the vampire with a 
	preternatural calm, no sounds originate from the area directly around 
	the vampire, therefore masking the death screams of his victims. 

[**] 	Weakness 'target' - This allows the vampire to transform his own blood 
	into poison and infect the body of his victim, lowering their strength. 

[***] 	Infirmity 'target' - This is similar to weakness only more devastating, 
	and has a wider range of affects on the target. 

[****] 	Bloodagony - With this power the vampire is able to poison any weapon 
	with his own blood, increasing the combat bonuses on it and granting it 
	the ability to do aggravated damage. 

[*****]	Spit 'target' - At this level of mastery the vampire is actually able to
	spit his own blood at his opponents, transforming it once again into 
	venomous liquid that inflicts devastating injuries and aggravated damage. 
~

0 DAIMOINON~

[*] 	Guardian - This lets the vampire call upon the power of hell and summon 
	a demon to aid them as needed. 

[**] 	Fear 'target' - By using this power the vampire is able to send those 
	who listen to them into fits of terror at the damnation that awaits them 
	in the afterlife, rendering them incapable of hostile actions. 

[***] 	Portal 'target' - When the vampire reaches this level of the discipline 
	they gain the ability to call forth a portal through hell that reaches 
	out to other players, allowing them to travel to them, providing the 
	intended target has their summon on. 

[****] 	Curse 'target' - This will let the vampire call forth a terrible curse 
	on their victims actually causing their limbs to wither up and fall off 
	of their bodys. 

[*****]	Soultwist - The good fear this power for it allows the user to reach into
	their very being and attempt to rip out their soul, in fact the more pure 
	the target the more damage that is done. If this wasn't enough, at this 
	level of power the vampire gains resistance to heat and fire, preparing 
	them for their final passage to hell. 

[*****]	Servant: A much stronger version of Guardian.

[*****]	Baal: Allow the demon god Baal to possess you, increasing your abilities.

[*****]	Flames - Shoot flames from you finger tips at your target.
~

0 MELPOMINEE~

[*] 	Scream 'target' - has chance of stunning victim, or all in room 

[**] 	Reina - Make the room a safe room, for 60 seconds. 

[***] 	Courage - stops target from being dread gazed, feared etc 

[****] 	Love - make victim fall in love with user, ie can be ordered at anytime. 

[*****] Anger - similer to a frenzy, without actually frenzying, ie the target 
	attacks.
~

0 THANATOSIS~

[*] 	Hagswrinkles - look like any player or mob. 

[**] 	Putrefaction - rots victim. (Slowly lowers con) 

[***] 	Ashes - you can turn into an object and be safe etc. 

[****] 	Withering - removes peoples limbs. 

[*****]	Drainlife - takes hp/mana/move (may just be hp) and adds it to your own. 
~


0 CHIMERSTRY~

[*] 	Mirror - This allows the vampire to form a mirror image of himself 
	which will look	exactly as he does but once forced to interact with 
	the real world it will vanish completely. 

[**] 	Formillusion 'target' - This will form an exact copy of the target 
	and it will be every bit as real to the beholder as real people, however 
	upon death destruction is complete and no traces will remain. 

[***] 	Clone 'target' - The vampire that uses this has the ability to completely 
	clone objects making exact duplicates that are every bit as real and as 
	powerful as the original, however the it is only really an illusion and 
	as time passes so will the clone. 

[****] 	Falseappearance 'object' - By using this power the vampire gains the 
	ability to change the name and description of a object. 

[*****]	Control 'target' - At this final level of mastery the vampire actaully 
	gains the power	to control his illusions and may command them to do his 
	bidding but using [<command>.

[*****]	Truedisguise - change to look like a mob. 
~

0 DOMINATE~

This discipline reflects the mystical ability of vampires to influence 
the minds and actions of others.  Dominate is an aspect of the power of 
the mind and the will.

This Discipline allows the following powers:

[*] 	Command 'target' 'order' - By intruding upon a subject's mind the 
	vampire can impose a one-word command which will be instantly obeyed, 
	however this will only work upon those who are weak of will. 

[**] 	Condition 'target' - Through manipulation and subtle temptation, a 
	vampire can make their subject more pliant to suggestion, to the point 
	where they will always obey their commands once they have been fully 
	conditioned. 

[***] 	Possesion 'target' - This power allows the vampire to perform the atrocity 
	of taking complete control of another's body and mind. By stealing their 
	mind the vampire has complete control over them and may use their body 
	as freely as their own by using [. 

[****] 	Loyalty 'target' - This assures the loyalty of the target to the vampire, 
	they will believe that the vampire is their master, meaning that they will 
	always obey their commands and will never be able to bring themselves to 
	harm them. 
~

0 EMBRACE~
How to make a new vampire: 
Get the target to lower their defences 
Embrace <target> 
Embrace again when they are on the verge of death to stop 
Slit <left/right> 
Feed <target> 
Lick <left/right> 
Target is now a vampire. 
~

0 GOLCONDA~
Golconda is the state of being wherin the vampire manages to control her
frenzies and restrain the Beast. All kindred of clear minds seek this
state unless they want a total release from their Undeath. Golconda is a
very hard state of being to attain, but for many it is the only goal worth
attaining. Golconda is the final acceptance of ones curse and the
subsequant power over it. Central and basic to this is the act of remorse.
This is a personal and immediate realization of the sins one has commited.
Penance must be be performed and the worse one's sins, the more the
vampire needs to do. Once the beast has completly taken over (100 beast)
and you have lost control over your humanity (0 humanity) the attainment
of golconda is no longer possible. Your humanity and beast are
inextricably linked so that 80 humanity represents 20 beast. While 0 beast
when you attain Golconda is 100 humanity. Attaining golconda allows you
the ability to resist damage from sunlight and also rewards you with vast
experience. The true route to Golconda is known by few who closely guard
its secrets but it is believed to be closely linked to the power of Obeah
and to the vampire's experience. 
ALSO, type Controlbeast.
~
0 FANGS~
Fangs give you an extra bite attack when they are extended 
~ 
0 CLAWS~
Claws give you a cool flaming claws attack that does aggravated damage
when your hands are on fire. In case ya didnt know aggravated damage is
damage that you cant regen you have to cast heal to heal it.
Claws also have to be extended by typing claws.
~
0 HOOVES~
Hooves allow a demon to kick through the immunity to kick.
~
0 NIGHTSIGHT~
Nightsight gives you the ability to see in the dark. It is alot better
than infravision cause you can see everything,not just mobs.Nightsight
is activated by typing nightsight.
~
0 WINGS~
Wings allow you to go to the places that you would normally have to
cast fly to get to.
~
0 MIGHT~
Might gives you the power to flex and break ropes when tied.
~
0 TOUGHNESS~
Toughness reduces the damage inflicted to you.
~
0 SPEED~
Speed raises your attack speed.
~
0 TRAVEL~
Travel allows you to travel to any demon in your clan at will at any
given time. If a demon in another clan has their summon on you may travel
to them as well. It is a nifty trick when you are stuck in a no recall
room to type travel hell, that works from anywhere in the mud.
~
0 VISION~

Each level of Vision provides the demon with a new power, in the order as
follows: Heighten Readaura Unveil Astral Scry.

Heighten allows the demon to see invisible/hidden objects and people.
Readaura lets you read objects or characters, whilst Unveil allows the
demon to read a characters thoughts. Astral allows travel through the
spirit world and Scry allows the user to find the location of players/mobs
on the mud who are unshielded. Additionally, for each level of Vision
possessed, the demon is able to see through an equivalent level of Vampire
Obfuscate.
~

0 MOVE~
Move allows you to move while in weaponform by typing Roll <direction
you want to go in>.
~

0 LEAP~
Leap allows you to leap from the ground to a players inv,a mobs inv,or
in a pit of somesort ie. the donation pit.
~

0 MAGIC~
Magic gives you the ability to cast spells in weaponform. 
~

0 LIFESPAN~
Lifespan give a demon the power to live longer as a head after being
decapitated.A demon can cast some spells with this ability as a head.
~

0 PACT~
Pact gives you the ability to pact demons as in make another character
a demon.It also changes a demons rank from lesser demon to greater demon.
~

0 PRINCE~
Prince gives the ability to make demons, make demonarmour, and
gives you the ability to inpart powers to yourself and other demons in
your clan.It also turns a demon from a greater demon into a prince.
~

0 LONGSWORD SHORTSWORD~
This is the ability to transform into a demonic blade crafted from
demonsteel.
When wielded a demonsword will add +50 to hitroll and damroll.Also a demon
cannot be killed in weaponform and in this form a demon can be transported
to any mob or player with transport on.
~

0 EYESPY~
Leaves an eye belonging to the demon using the power, as a spy.
~

0 INFERNO~
When you become mortally wounded, using this power will cause anyone in
the room to suffer an amount of damage whilst simultaneously bringing you
back from the brink of death.
~

0 DEMONFORM~
This is a gift from Satan himself this allows you to transform
into the true form of a demon. This adds hit/dam and damcap.
~

0 DEMONARMOUR~
Syntax: demonarmour 'colour' 'armour' 
NB - This command can be used by Lords and Princes only.

Colour can be one of: Black Grey Purple Red Brass.
Armour can be one of: Ring Collar Plate Helmet Leggings Boots Gauntlets
Sleeves Cape Belt Bracer Visor.

Black armour costs 0 quest points per piece.
Grey armour costs 100 quest points per piece.
Purple armour costs 250 quest points per piece.
Red armour costs 750 quest points per piece.
Brass armour costs 1500 quest points per piece.
Each piece of armour also costs 5000 demon points of power.

If you sacrifice demon armour the quest points and demon points are
returned to you so it helps to make armour as soon as you can and upgrade
as you go.
~
0 DEMONPOINTS~
Demon points are what demons use to buy their powers with. Demon points
are gained by killing mobs or killing players.In order to recieve powers
from your lord you may type pray and this will give your lord all of your
current demon points.In order to get powers from a prince you must make
a demon point token.This is done by typing dptoken <amount>.
~
0 INPART~
Angels:
Fangs (2500), Claws (2500), Hooves (1500), Nightsight (3000),
Wings (1000), Might (7500), Toughness (7500), Speed (7500), Travel (1500),
Scry (7500), Shadowsight (7500), Move (500), Leap (500), Magic (1000),
Lifespan (100), Pact (0), Prince (0), Longsword (0), Shortsword (0),
Demonform (25000), Imp (10000), Inferno (10000), Eyespy (1000), Firewall (1000)
Vision (10000 per increase), Daimoinon (10000 per increase).

Demons:
Fangs (2500), Claws (2500), Hooves (1500), Nightsight (3000),
Wings (1000), Might (7500), Toughness (7500), Speed (7500), Travel (1500),
Scry (7500), Shadowsight (7500), Move (500), Leap (500), Magic (1000),
Lifespan (100), Pact (0), Prince (0), Longsword (0), Shortsword (0),
Demonform (25000), Imp (10000), Inferno (10000), Eyespy (1000), Firewall (1000)
Vision (10000 per increase), Daimoinon (10000 per increase).

Type 'help Ainparts' for specific help on angel inparts. 
Type 'help Dinparts' for specific help for demons.
~
0 AINPARTS AINPART~
Aura - The ability to extend an angelic aura,
adding an extra attack.

Claws - The ability to extend claws of white fire from your gauntlets,
giving assistance in unarmed fighting.

Feet - Extend a nimbus over your feet, giving the ability to kick through immune.

Nightsight - The ability to see in the dark.

Wings - The ability to extend wings from your back.
Syntax: wings unfold

Might - Gives the angel the might of their god. Increased
damcap, and hit damage.

Toughness - Angelic Resistance. Gives resistance to
weapons.

Speed - Enables use of angelic power to fuel speed. The more power used, the greater the
speed while the power lasts.

syntax: speed <number of minutes (1-10)>

Travel - The ability to Travel to any other angel of your lord at
will.

Scry - The ability to see over long distances.

Shadowsight - The ability to see in the umbra. 
Syntax: Umbralvision

Move - The ability to roll as a weapon. 
Syntax: Roll <direction>

Leap - The ability to leap as a weapon.

Magic - The ability to cast spells as a weapon.

For more inparts, check help AINPART2

~
0 AINPART2 AINPARTS2~

Lifespan - The ability to disintigrate faster, and use
certain abilities as a head.

Pact - The ability to make another angel.

Prince - Angel Lord Only. Allows the angel lord to
promote the angel to prince.

Longsword - Ability to transform into an angelic longsword. 
Syntax: weaponform

Shortsword - Ability to transform into an angelic shortsword. 
Syntax: weaponform

Angelform - Ability to use angelic energy to change into a beautiful angel.

Gives hit/dam/ac bonus. Unable to talk properly while
in angelform.

Allows Wing Attack
syntax: wattack

Cherub - Brings a Cherub to your assistance. Will tell
you when there is a skill being used on you, and will
transport items.

Inferno - The ability to create a blazing inferno in
the room, damaging everyone in it. This can only be
used while morted.

Eyespy - The ability to take out an eye and use it as
a spy. Syntax to control eye: [(command)

Windwall - The ability to create a wall of buffering wind, which prevents any without
angelic mastery of the wind from passing through without falling to the ground.

Vision - Levels of vision for an angel. Each level
provides, in this order, Heighten, Readaura, Unveil,
Astral, Scry. For more information, try help VISION.

Rejuvenation - The holy area of an angel's aresenal of
skills. Each level will do the following, in order,
spiritshare, strengthen, guardianangel, purify, Empower. For more
information, try help REJUVENATION.

Extra skills - 

Flaming Hands - Engulfs your hands in a holy flame.
Syntax: hands

Halo - The ability to extend your angelic halo.
Gives an extra attack.

Orb - The ability to fly to any person

Wing Attack - While in angelform, strike with white
energy for damage.
syntax: wattack
~
0 DINPART DINPARTS~

Fangs - The ability to extend fangs from your gums.
Gives an extra attack.

Claws - The ability to extend claws from your fingers.
Assists in unarmed fighting.

Hooves - The ability to transform your feet into
hooves. Allows kicks to go through immune.

Nightsight - The ability to see in the dark.

Wings - The ability to extend wings from your back.
Syntax: Wings unfold

Might - The Power of Hell. Might gives increased
damcap, and hit damage.

Toughness - Demonic Toughness. Gives weapon
resistance.

Speed - The ability to move at supernatural speed
(auto). This increases the demon's hit %/parry/dodge.

Travel - The ability to travel to other demons. Only
works to those of the same clan.

Scry - The ability to scry over long distances.

Shadowsight - The ability to see into the umbra.
Syntax: Umbralvision

Move - The ability to roll as a weapon. Syntax: roll
<direction>

Leap - The ability to leap as a weapon.

Magic - The ability to cast spells as a weapon.


Try help DINPART2 DINPARTS2
~
0 DINPART2 DINPARTS2~

Lifespan - The ability to use some skills while
decapitated. Also allows a demon to disintigrate
faster.

Pact - The ability to make a new demon.

Prince - The ability to promote a regular demon to
Prince. This can only be used by a Demon Lord.

Longsword - The ability to transform into a demonic
longsword. Syntax: Weaponform.

Shortsword - The ability to transform into a demonic
shortsword. Syntax: Weaponform.

Demonform - The ability to transform into a huge,
hulking demon. This gives bonus hit/dam/ac. You cannot
talk properly while in demonform.

Imp - The ability to summon a messanger. This will
tell you when others are using skills on you. This
will also transport items. Syntax: Imp (object)
(player or mob).

Inferno - The ability to create an inferno in the
room. This will damage everyone in the room. This can
only be used while morted.

Eyespy - The ability to create a familiar in the form
of an eye. Syntax to command eye: [<command>

Firewall - The ability to create a wall of fire. Any
person walking through will be hurt.

Vision - These are the levels of vision for a demon.
In this order, per level, Heighten, Readaura, Unveil,
Astral, Scry. Help VISION for more information. Note:
The astral is used in the same way as an eyespy.

Daimoinon - The Demonic Powers of a demon. In this
order, per level, Guardian, Fear, Portal, Curse,
Soultwist, Servant, Baal, Flames. Help DAIMOINON for
more information. Note: There are only five levels of
daimoinon.

Extra Abilities

Horns - The ability to extend horns from your head.
Gives additional attack.

Flaming Hands - The ability to engulf your hands in
flames.

Engulf - The ability to engulf your target in flames,
doing damage. 
~
0 FIREWALL~

Creates a burning wall of flames that causes fire damage to anyone walking
through it.
~
0 ENGULF~

A free power enabling the demon to engulf his foes in combat, causing them
fire damage every few rounds. Also can be used with no target to provide
the demon with flaming hands.
~
0 HORNS~

A free power giving demons a headbutt attack.
~
0 IMP~

Calls up an imp on the shoulder, that informs the demon when he is being
scryed or read by a player. Also provides the ability to transfer an item
to another player if their 'trans' is on.
~

0 ABOM ABOMINATION BAALI BSD LICH NEPHANDI SKINDANCER HYBRID~
Hybrids:
                Abomination  ==  Vampire/Werewolf
                Baali        ==  Vampire/Demon
                BSD          ==  Demon/Werewolf
                Lich         ==  Vampire/Mage
                Nephandi     ==  Mage/Demon
                Skindancer   ==  Mage/Werewolf

Hybrids are able to purchase, and wear armor from both classes.
They are also have limited abilities from both classes.
~

0 BEAST~

Vampires, like mortals, are creatures of instinct.  However, the 
instincts of the vampire are those of a hunter, not a gatherer.  Vampires 
are the ultimate predators and stand at the apex of the food chain.  
They are highly developed killing machines - the harbringers of death.
For vampires to survive in modern society, however, they must learn to 
keep the Beast in check.  The instincts of violence (the Beast) so 
essential in the wild serve only to endanger the vampire in today's 
complex world.  The Beast's rage has its uses, but the blindness it 
creates far outweighs its benefits.
Vampires struggle to suppress the Beast, but, no matter how hard they 
try, they do not always prevail, and when it gets loose, the havoc it 
creates goes far beyond the horror of any mortal rage.
~

0 FAVOUR SIRE PRINCE~
Syntax: favour <target> <sire/prince>

Favour is an ability available to second generation vampires and vampire 
princes.

SIRE allows the target vampire of your clan to sire another vampire.  
Once a single vampire has been created the power is lost, but can be 
granted again if the Antediluvian or Prince so desire.  A childe sired 
without permission is known as an Anarch.

PRINCE turns the target vampire into a prince, who is then able to allow 
other vampires the ability to sire more vampires still.  Only an 
Antediluvian has the power to make some a prince (or to remove the 
prince's powers).

ACCEPT will accept a childe into the clan, making them a Neonate.

INDUCT and OUTCAST will accept an Anarch into the clan or outcast a member.
~

0 BREED POWERS~
Werewolf breeds
               +-+-+-+-+-+   +-+-+   +-+-+-+   +-+-+-+-+-+
	       |B|r|e|e|d|   |o|f|   |t|h|e|   |G|a|r|o|u|
	       +-+-+-+-+-+   +-+-+   +-+-+-+   +-+-+-+-+-+

                     Homid        Metis      Lupus
~


0 HOMID~
- Persuasion - Syantax: Persuasion - This power makes you more attractive to 
animals.
- Staredown - Syntax: Staredown (target) - This power can make the enemy 
flee in terror.
- Reshape - Syntax: Reshape (object) (description) - This power allows you 
to rename objects.
**note** That if you have this power you should probably use it instead of
wasting quest points on 'quest <object> <name/long/short>'.
- Disquiet - Disquiet (target) - You stare at the enemy. Making it hard for 
them to concentrate.
**note** That this is a curse (-25 hit/dam) and that if you type disquiet
without a target you will use it on yourself.
~

0 METIS~
- Nightsight - Syntax: Nightsight - This causes your eyes to glow green.
Allowing you to see in the dark
- Burrow - Syntax: Burrow - This allows you to burrow into the ground. Where 
none can attack.
- Witherlimb - Syntax: Witherlimb (target) - This power withers the limbs 
off its victims.
- Porcupine - Syntax: Porcupine - This makes quills extend from your back.
**note** Can only be activated in Crinos form (rage)
~

0 LUPUS~
- Heighten - Syntax: Heighten - this power allows you to see more things.
- Beckon - Syntax: Beckon (animal) - With this power you can beckon animals 
to o your bidding.
- Master - Syntax: Master - This power, like Persuasion, makes you more
attractive to animals - they won't attack
- Masssummons - Syntax: Masssumons - You summon any beckoned beast on the mud.
- Fleshbond - Syntax: Fleshbond (animal) - You gain extra hps by bonding 
with an animal.
~

