0 CLANLEADERS LEADERS CLANLEADER~
#0Welcome to the ranks of leadership. With this there are a few rules you
need to follow.

1. #RRespect the imms#0 - New and younger players will be looking up to
you for guidance. This is a no-tolerance issue.

2. #RMaintain your weekly hours #0- There is a minimum of 10 hours a week
that all CL's must maintain to keep their positions. If you are unable to
meet these due to vacation, illness, etc. Please note the imms on board 5,
and your position shall be kept for you upon your return.

3. #RDo not class newbies#0 - This one is for their sake. Unless you know
the person can play the class well and not get killed often, then don't
class them under a minimum of 5k across. You may raise the requirements to
meet your clan's needs. We want to keep players not PK them into oblivion.

Follow those rules and you'll do just fine. If you have any questions
please direct them to your class leader. (type help class).

If you would like your requirements posted please type HELP CLANREQS
~

0 CLANREQS~

#0To post your clan requirements in a help file (ex. HELP FIRE) You need
to do the following.

#R1.#0 Please write them out, and put all color codes (Type help color) in
the
file. Do NOT write the color name. If you do not put the codes in, I will
not post them until corrected.

#R2. #0Help files will not be edited. They go in as you type them.

#R3. #0If you do decide to use colors, then please use colors that are
easy on the eyes. And absolutely NO blinkies. I'll slay you myself if you even
suggest that. >:)

#R4.#0 When emailing, please put in the subject CLANNAME HELP FILE. It
doesn't have this subject its easily missed in my mass emails that I receive.

#R5.#0 You can email them to ravyn@sbcglobal.net

#R6.#0 Please expect a 24 hour turnaround unless otherwise
noted. (Vacations..etc etc etc.)

#0Have fun with the help files. They're there to entice people into your
clan. You can have RP's, Requirements, etc etc. Take a look at the other
examples.#n
~ 

