0 MP MULTIPLAY MULTIPLAYING~

Multiplaying consists of the following, and will be dealt with
accordingly.

1. Two players sharing a single character.
2. Using two different characters to help kill a mob/player.
3. Transferring of equipment from one character to another.
4. Having two characters on from the same IP at once. Including link-dead
   characters.
5. Taking IC issues from one character to another. (ex. Getting killed on
   one character and then bringing on a more powerful character to kill
   the person who killed you.)

Please see HELP PUNISHMENT
~
0 MULTIKILL SPAMKILL PK~
Here are the specifics to which the Gods and Goddesses of the Realm have
decided upon.

1. It is multikill if a player is killed more than three times in a period
of 5 minutes.
2. Do not leave a head unsacced, as this will be considered as leaving
them morted. 

If these rules are broken, the guilty party shall be punished

Please see HELP PUNISHMENT
~   

0 ROLEPLAYING RP FLAME~

Roleplay Roleplaying Chat Flame IC

To be counted as a roleplayer and use the roleplay channels (chat and 
flame), make a sincere attempt to roleplay.

Some basic guidelines to roleplaying:

Don't fight with the people out of character that your character doesn't 
like.

Do have an idea for a background. Not a big thing, just an idea about why 
your character is the way he or she is.

Do have a somewhat defined personality and character.

Don't use roleplay to justify picking fights only with people far smaller 
than you.

Do have fun
~

0 NOTEPAPER LETTER~
Syntax: Scribe <what you wish to scribe>
Syntax: Peruse note (to read the note)
Syntax: Seal note (to seal the note)
Syntax: Unseal note (to unseal the note)

1) to create paper - q create notepaper (10 qps)
2) Hold the paper in one hand
3) scribe <message> (only one line so far, but the line can be 
    as long as it needs to be)
3) seal the note with your personal tamper-proof seal with 'seal note'
4) deliver via courier or transportation spell to suit your Roleplay needs.
 
To read them you just hold the sealed note, Unseal the note,
and 'peruse' it.
 
Remember to sign your letters, so the addressee knows if it was opened! 
~

